BALI: Saudi Foreign Minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan met his Indian counterpart Dr. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar in the Indonesian island of Bali on Thursday. The meeting was held on the sidelines of a gathering between the foreign ministers representing the G20 countries. The ministers discussed Saudi-Indian bilateral relations across several fields of joint cooperation, sharing opportunities to enhance their links to achieve more stability and prosperity for the two friendly countries and peoples. The meeting was attended by the Saudi Ambassador to Indonesia Essam Al-Thaqafi, and the director general of the office of the minister of foreign affairs, Abdulrahman Al-Daoud.